modName: GD's Skyrim Reshaded - Performance Reshade Presets for Purity ELFX RLO
summary:
Skyrim reshaded is a collection of presets for Reshade that will give your game a brand new look without killing performances like ENBs.
The presets are tailored to be used with lighting/weather mods like Purity, ELFX or RLO
You will have a wide variety of color grading presets to choose from.
descriptionHtml:
[center][color=#6fa8dc][size=6]Skyrim Reshaded
[/size][/color]
[youtube]f5jSjzDZCfA[/youtube][/center]

[center][color=#cfe2f3][size=6][u]Description
[/u][/size][/color][/center][size=4]
Skyrim Reshaded is a Reshade preset that will enhance the look of your game using various post processing shaders. It is meant to be used with Purity and ELFX/RLO but will work with any lighting mod.
It is performance friendly, but you can expect around 3 to 5 FPS lost, maybe less.

I divided the mod in two parts :

 [color=#6aa84f]- [/color][/size][color=#6aa84f][size=5]The visuals enhancements.[/size][/color][size=4] This contains general shaders for making your game look better without changing the overall feel. The game will generally be more realistic. Here is a list of the effects used:

[/size][list]
[*][size=4][s]SSDO [i](PPFX Shaderpack)[/i] : SSDO adds screen-space AO and faked GI. For those no familiar with these terms, this shader will add some shadows to make the game less flat and better shaded and simulate bouncing colors.[/s] Disabled as it was too buggy[/size]
[*][size=4]Bloom [i](PPFX Shaderpack)[/i]: This is a subtle but nice effect. Allows strong lights to bleed their color.[/size]
[*][size=4]Ambient Light [i](GemFX)[/i] : This is a brillant shader. You can think of it as similar to bloom, but the effect is way more effective. It blends all the other effects to give a good looking final image.[/size]
[*][size=4]DPX [i](SweetFX)[/i][/size]
[*][size=4]Vignette[i] (SweetFX)[/i][/size]
[*][size=4]Godrays [i](PPFX shaderpack)[/i] : nice godrays not to over the top. ([u]Cinematic version only[/u])[/size]
[/list][list]
[*][size=4]Tuning palette : see below[/size]
[/list][size=4]
Changelog :
V2.1   : Added FXAA antialiasing. [u]Please disable the antialiasing in the launcher[/u]
V2.00 : Heavy tweaking of the Ambient Light shader
Added subtle vignette effect
Lens dirt removed from the cinematic version
v1.01 : SSDO now disabled by default
v1.00 : initial release

[/size]
[color=#6aa84f][size=5] - The Color grading.[/size][/color][size=4]The tuning palette effects allows advanced color grading. Combined with the visual enhancements, this allows to deeply change the look of your game using LUT (look up table). I already made several presets and you can make you own if you like (It's very fun). See below


Here are the presets. It's hard to swowcase the presets with only one screenshot, so the best is that you try trusting the description ;) 

[color=#6aa84f][u]Mother Nature[/u] [/color](New!) : A nature-focused preset. Strong greens and blues outside, strong yellows inside. I strongly suggest using this preset alongside mods like Flora overhaul or Verdant for a lush look.

[img]http://static-6.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/66171-0-1432457225.jpg[/img]


[size=4][color=#6aa84f] Lean World[/color] (New!) : Really hard to explain this one. I would say it make the land look dry and a bit arid. An interesting one to play with, changes the feel of the game a lot, but may not look good in every condition. I really like it though so may be worth a try :)

[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/66171-0-1432449613.jpg[/img]
[/size]
[img]http://static-4.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/66171-1-1432449613.jpg[/img]

[u][color=#6aa84f]Vibrant Realism[/color][/u] (included by default) : Gives the game a more colorful yet realitic look. I recommend it for most users
[img]http://static-3.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/66171-0-1432376595.jpg[/img]

[u][color=#6aa84f]Dead World[/color][/u] : Gives a post-apo look to the game. There will still be a warm feel in interiors. If you want a depressed world this the one for you. There's a civil war going on there after all, not to mention the dragons ...
[img]http://static-3.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/66171-1-1432376595.jpg[/img][/size]
[size=4]
[u][color=#6aa84f]The Cold North[/color][/u] : Gives Skyrim this cold harsh look it deserved. Perfect for a hardcore playthrough. It's meant to give the game a very realistic harsh look.
[img]http://static-3.nexusmods.com/15/mods/110/images/66171-2-1432376595.jpg[/img][/size]


[size=4]I'll probably be making more of these, I really like it. If you have the time, I strongly suggest you do your own too ! I've uploaded my psd file with a lot of screenshots to work with.[/size]
[size=4]I could try to make a tutorial if it's a popular request. But english is not my native language so be warned ! ;)
Or you can just tell ma what kind of preset you'd like. If you post a comment where you explain what you'd like and post a reference I'll try to do it.
[/size]

[size=6][center]Compatibility and installation[/center][/size][size=4]
[u]Compatibility[/u] : This is compatible with every mod except others post-processing injectors like ENBs, SweetFX or GemFX presets. That being said, SweetFX and GemFX are both included in Reshade, so you could import a preset really easily to combine it with this mod.

ReShade should be compatible with ENBoost, but some extra steps are needed :
[list]
[*][size=4]Install ReShade[/size]
[*][size=4]rename d3d9.dll (in your Skyrim folder) into reshade_d3d9.dll[/size]
[*][size=4]Install ENBoost[/size]
[*][size=4]In the .ini file for the ENB edit the folowing lines :[/size]
[/list]
[PROXY]
EnableProxyLibrary=true
InitProxyFunctions=true
ProxyLibrary=reshade_d3d9.dll

However it seems like it's not working for everyone so if you encounter "the game stopped working", then you'll have to disable either ReShade or ENBoost


[u]Installation[/u] :
[list]
[*][size=4]Unistall any ENB/SweetFX you would have already installed[/size]
[*][size=4](optionnal) Intall your favorites lighting mods : I recommend [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/65242/?]Purity[/url] and [url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/27043/?]ELFX[/url]. Pure Weather, Climates of Tamriel, Realisitc lighting overhaul are fine too. You can install Dynavision too for dynamic DoF.[/size]
[*][size=4]Go to [url=http://reshade.me/]this page[/url] and download "ReShade + framework"[/size]
[*][size=4]Launch "Reshade Setup"[/size]
[*][size=4]Click "select game" and select TESV.exe (in your Skyrim folder)[/size]
[*][size=4]Now download Skyrim Reshaded. I do not recommend the cinematic version. It's a bit less perf friendly and the lens dirts destroys some details in the sky. Your choice though.[/size]
[*][size=4]Put "ppfx", "Reshade", and "reshade.fx" in your Skyrim folder[/size]
[*][size=4]Disable bDeferredShadows in Skyrimprefs.ini if it was enabled[/size]
[*][size=4]You're ready to go ! :)[/size]
[*][size=4](optionnal) Vibrant Realism is installed by default. If you want to change it just download the LUT you want put the ReShade folder in the Skyrim folder and overwrite.[/size]
[*][size=4]Don't forget to leave an comment if you have any suggestion and to leave an endorsment if you like the mod ! [/size]
[/list]
[u]Uninstallation[/u]
[list]
[*][size=4]Simply delete de d3d9.dll. (Or reshade_d3d9.dll if you're using ENBoost)[/size]
[*][size=4]You can also delete ppfx, ReShade, ReShade.fx, d3d9.log if you want to keep your Skyrim folder clean[/size]
[/list]
The screenshots were taken with only Vanilla, purity and ELFX, so if you like it screenshots or video are more than welcome ! :)
You can also check my other mods :
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/63803/?]GD's Farmhouse - A 2k farmhouse retexture[/url]
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/64225/?]GD's Cow - A 2k highlandcow retexture[/url]
[url=http://www.nexusmods.com/skyrim/mods/64057/?]GD's Steam Centurion - A 2k centurion retexture for M.H.A.R.P.H.I.N

[/url][u]Credits[/u]
I'm not the maker of Reshade. I'm not the maker of the shaders. I've just tweaked it to my own liking and made some color grading
Credits for ReShade and the shaders go to Crosire, Euda, LuciferHawk, CeeJay, Marty MacFly.
If you liked this mod, go and check the ReShade website : [url=http://reshade.me/]http://reshade.me/[/url] They're making an awesome job and ReShade is regularly updated and it will soon replace SweetFX. They anounced a configurator so if you don't like working with congifuration files you'll just have to wait a bit. Check the forums too, there's already a huge amount of shaders to choose from, and making a preset is really fun !
[/size][size=4]
[/size]
